get.summary:
List all direct debit payments in a customer environment with optional filters applied.
                Filters that can be applied:
                No filter: GET v1/customer/debit/mandates - list all direct debit payments in customer environment - owned either by himself or by any of his endusers.
                By mandate : GET v1/customer/debit/mandates?mandate_id=UUID list payments by mandate
                By ledger : GET v1/customer/debit/mandates?ledger_id=UUID list debit payments connected with supplied ledger.
                By ledger holder: GET v1/customer/debit/mandates?holder_id=UUID list debit payments by supplied holder, enduser or customer himself.

get.summary:
Get compliance manual that includes all the firewalls and related data,
                 optionally at some specific point in time
get.description:
Get compliance manual that includes all the firewalls and related data,
                 optionally at some specific point in time.
                 The firewall rules are coded in special lisp-like syntax
                 and are executed whenever customer creates new enduser or new transaction. The
                 firewall type configures, which of these options the firewall should verify.

post.description:
Set/update firewall rules. The firewall rules are coded in special lisp-like syntax
                and are executed whenever customer creates new enduser or new transaction. The
                firewall type configures, which of these options the firewall should verify.
                Please keep in mind that any update of rules, even submitting the same data, leads to use of all current datasets.
                This can lead to different firewall results, even if the rules themselves have not been altered

name_on_card.description: The cardholder's name to be printed or embossed on the card. It accepts ISO basic Latin alphabet and can be up to 21 characters long including spaces.

partner_product.description: Human readable identifier of the Railsbank product that provides card functionality.

card_carrier_type.description: The carrier type to be used for the card when delivered.

address_city.description: The city or locality. Mandatory when card_type is physical

address_iso_country.description: The ISO country code. Mandatory when card_type is physical

address_postal_code.description: The zip code or postal code. Mandatory when card_type is physical

address_refinement.description: The address refinement, may include flat number, house name etc

address_region.description: The state, province, prefecture, or region

address_street.description: The street name. Mandatory when card_type is physical

card_delivery_address.description: The physical address where the card will be sent to. Mandatory when card_type is physical

card_delivery_method.description: The shipping method used to deliver the card, if delivery address is outside the UK, it must be international-mail

card_delivery_name.description: The name which the delivery will be addressed to (can differ from cardholder name).

card_design.description: The card design to be used for the card when issued, from the list of Railsbank configured card designs.

name_on_card.description: The cardholder's name to be printed or embossed on the card. It accepts ISO basic Latin alphabet and can be up to 21 characters long including spaces.

qr_code_content.description: The string to be encoded in the auto-generated QR code on a physical card. For example, a URL, SMS message, in app action, an event etc.

example.qr_code_content: Any reasonably long string, e.g. description of something

card_id.description: Railsbank's unique identifier for the card.

post.description:
DEPRECATED in favour of `/v1/customer/beneficiaries/{beneficiary_id}/idv-docs` endpoint.
                 Upload new identity verification document for beneficiary.

Creates new fx transaction. The assets are sent from specific endusers ledger to the
     given beneficiary. Note that the transaction may take some time (days in some cases)
     to pass through all stages of processing. During this time out can fetch the
     transaction and see if it is already in the 'done' state.

amount.description: The amount of the fixed_side currency to be converted

beneficiary_account_id.description: The Railsbank Beneficiary account ID to be credited. This needs to be set only when sending to an account that isn't the beneficiary's default

beneficiary_id.description: The receiving Railsbank Beneficiary ID. This needs to be set only if sending to the default beneficiary's account

fixed_side.description: Sets the base currency for pair rate direction, which determines how much the base currency is worth as measured against the second currency. It assures if the amount specified will either be debited from the sending ledger or credited in the receiving account

ledger_from_id.description: The Railsbank Ledger ID to be debited

payment_method.description: Sets if transaction will be sent via local (e.g. UKFP) or international (e.g. Swift) payment schemes

reason.description: Text the enduser can add to the transaction for the beneficiary

reference.description: Additional text to be passed with the transaction

transaction_meta.description: An object allowing custom fields that can be created and stored against the transaction

get.summary: Get list of ledgers that were modified from the time specified
get.description:
Get list of ledgers that were modified from the time specified. Note that this call
                is optimized to be quite fast - you can call it frequently to check out, if there
                are some changes on any ledgers. Interval which we query is closed in from-time
                and returned next-request-date. That mean if ledger amount has beet updated at
                exact moment of next-request-date this ledger will be included in previous and next answer.
